The Middle East is at the crossroads of three continents: Asia, Africa, and Europe. It includes the countries of Bahrain, Cyprus, Egypt, Iran, Iraq, Israel, Jordan, Kuwait, Lebanon, Oman,

Some major cultures have emerged in this region throughout history:

1. Ancient Egyptian culture (circa 3150 BCE - 30 BCE) centered on religion and was one of the first civilizations to develop complex social hierarchies.

2. Mesopotamian culture (circa 4500 BCE - 539 BCE) developed various empires with distinctive features; it used cuneiform writing and employed mathematics for trade.

3. Phoenician culture (1600 BCE – 300 CE) was characterized by seafaring skills that led to extensive trading networks between coastal territories spanning modern-day Lebanon to Spain.
